<TITLE> Long-awaited ACH online from Nov: BB </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 21 (bdnews24.com) - Bangladesh Bank will officially introduce a long-awaited Automated Clearing House from next November to facilitate the country's banking and business activities. The facility will begin trial runs in October, Bangladesh Bank governor Atiur Rahman told reporters on Tuesday after a meeting with the chief executives of government, private and foreign owned banks. "Bangladesh Bank is prepared on every side to commence operation of the Automated Clearing House. This meeting was called to discuss the current status of preparedness of the banks," said the governor. "They assured us that they will be able to complete overall preparation by October. According to their assurance we can start fully operating the system from November." Rahman said the ACH will take just a few seconds to clear an inter-bank cheque, which now takes three to four days through the existing manual system. "BB has been working for a good number of days to get the system running. Now it has reached the final stage. "It is crucial the country's banking and business that a cheque issued by one bank can be automatically and instantly cleared in another bank." "It will save time, reduce complexity and the system will require less manpower", Rahman added. He said the ACH would be officially inaugurated by the prime minister in November. bdn
